<p>
A <a href="/docs/Fields">field</a> implementing the Choice <a href="/docs/Field_Types">field type</a> can store an index (integer) value for a selection in an array of possible choices specified by the field. Due to array convention, the first choice has an index of <code>0</code> rather than <code>1</code>. The Choice <a href="/docs/Field_Types">field type</a> has a single required parameter named <code>Choices</code> that must contain an array of strings.
</p>

<div class="heading">Example Field</div>
<pre>{
	"Name" : "My Choice Field",
	"Field Type" : "Choice",
	"Description" : "The example usage of the Choice Field Type.",
	"Required" : true,
	"Parameters" : {
		"Choices" : [
			"The first choice",
			"The second choice",
			"The third choice"
		]
	} 
}</pre>

<div class="heading">Example Value</div>
<pre>"ExampleUser.MyType.1" : {
	...
	"My Choice Field" : 1,//Corresponds to "The second choice".
	...
}</pre>